{
  "stem": "11964.2",
  "chunk_idx": 8,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 8.1,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "At first, they would tell us to surrender all our valuables, all our jewelry.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "Then they would tell us to surrender all our furs.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "Then we had to surrender blankets.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "Then they would come and ask us to surrender copper and nickel artifacts, anything that they could, could transfer into other implements of war.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "And they didn't just rest at the proclamations.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "They would have raids.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "And if they weren't satisfied at the number of items that they would collect, they would come, sometimes-- mostly-- in the middle of the night.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "And they would raid the apartments, and they would turn it upside down.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "And they would take whatever they could lay their hands on.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So those raids, at first, were for collecting things.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "But then they were doing raids for collecting people.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "As a young girl, how did your mind comprehend what was going on?",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I really cannot answer how my mind comprehended it.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I think that in situations, in emergency situations, what you do, you work on your instinct.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "You do not have enough time, or the luxury, to philosophize and try to analyze as to what does this mean to you-- to me.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "What we were worrying about is how to survive as a family unit, how to protect each other, and how to make sure that we don't lose dignity.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And the unfortunate thing is that this was the first thing we had to lose, is the dignity.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Because I remember one time when they came into the house, to the apartment, and they took my father and they started kicking him.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And my father looked at us and cried.",
      "word_count": 8
    }
  ],
